# Do not commit PDFs

Never stage or commit `.pdf` files. Raw papers live in `papers/` as
local-only input; keep the knowledge in Markdown notes (`notes/papers/`)
instead of committing the source PDFs.

- When staging changes, exclude `*.pdf` (e.g. `git add` specific files, or
  `git add -A` then `git reset -- '*.pdf'`).
- If a PDF is already staged, unstage it before committing.
- If asked to commit "everything", still leave PDFs out and mention that you
  skipped them.
